com.badlogic.gdx.ai.btree.decorator

Class Include<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.badlogic.gdx.ai.btree.Task<E>
      • com.badlogic.gdx.ai.btree.Decorator<E>
        • com.badlogic.gdx.ai.btree.decorator.Include<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of the blackboard object that tasks use to read or modify game state

    @TaskConstraint(minChildren=0,
                maxChildren=0)
public class Include<E>
extends Decorator<E>
    An Include decorator grafts a subtree. When the subtree is grafted depends on the value of the lazy parameter: at clone-time if is false, at run-time if is true.

    • Method Detail

      • setControl

        public void setControl(Task<E> control)
        The first call of this method lazily sets its child to the referenced subtree created through the BehaviorTreeLibraryManager, then invoke the same method of the superclass. Subsequent calls invoke the same method of the superclass directly since the child has already been set. A UnsupportedOperationException is thrown if this Include is eager.
